						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in front of the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>[Kākatīya Rudramadēvī.]</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Preamble describes the Kākatīya lineage up to Rudradevī (Rudramā) and refers to the consecration of several <hi rend="italic">liṅgas</hi> and to the grant of several villages including Velagapūṁḍi, Kommūru, Aitaprōlu etc., Viśvēśvaraśivāchārya is mentioned as the manager of the gift-villages.</p>						

						<p>(Cf. Malkapuram inscription of Rudrāṁbā which was published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.</hi> X, No. 395 and <hi rend="italic">Journal of the Andhra Historical Research Society,</hi> Vol. IV, pp. 147-164).</p>						

						</summary>
